{
    "organization": "podman-container-tools",
    "repository": "buildah",
    "number": 1,
    "type": "issue",
    "title": "Reading non-ociv1 image configs is lossy",
    "state": "closed",
    "labels": [
        "locked - please file new issue/PR"
    ],
    "user": "nalind",
    "body": "Right now the tool assumes that image configurations can be decoded as OCI image-spec v1 Image objects.  If the source image is anything else, we lose information this way.",
    "comments": [
        {
            "user": "nalind",
            "body": "We should be able to read `github.com/docker/docker/image.Image` configuration blobs now.  There's some information in manifests that decode as `github.com/containers/image/image.manifestSchema1` in images like kubernetes/pause where we don't have a config blob, and we might have to try fishing around in the manifest for them."
        },
        {
            "user": "rhatdan",
            "body": "Is this issue still present?"
        },
        {
            "user": "nalind",
            "body": "We handle images that include config blobs (version 2, schema 2), but we still don't support digging around in (version 2, schema 1) images."
        },
        {
            "user": "nalind",
            "body": "As of #118, we should be handling v2 schema 1 images, so I think we can finally close this one."
        }
    ],
